{"id":468610,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mumu","text":"Mumu () is a Russian tale. It was published in 1852 by Ivan Turgenev in the political magazine: \"Sovremennik\".\nThe story is about the relationship between Gerasim - a deaf mute servant - and his dog. The story changes to an elderly widow-woman who is Gerasim's boss. The woman shows her cruel side when she tells him to get rid of his pet.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Russian_literature","surface_form":"Russian tale","offset":13},{"uri":"Publish","surface_form":"publish","offset":34},{"uri":"Ivan_Turgenev","surface_form":"Ivan Turgenev","offset":55},{"uri":"Political","surface_form":"political","offset":76},{"uri":"Magazine","surface_form":"magazine","offset":86},{"uri":"Relationship","surface_form":"relationship","offset":134},{"uri":"Deafness","surface_form":"deaf mute","offset":167},{"uri":"Elderly","surface_form":"elderly","offset":224},{"uri":"Widow","surface_form":"widow","offset":232},{"uri":"Boss","surface_form":"boss","offset":261},{"uri":"Cruelty_to_animals","surface_form":"cruel side","offset":287},{"uri":"Pet","surface_form":"pet","offset":335}]}